def get_xy(size: tuple = (10,10)):
            u1 = np.random.binomial(n = 1, p = 0.2, size = size)
            u2 = np.random.binomial(n = 1, p = 0.1, size = size)
            x = 6*u1 + u2
            y = x.copy()
            orange = np.argwhere(y==7)
            for idx in orange:
                y[idx[0]+1:,idx[1]] = 4
                y[idx[0],idx[1]] = 3
            return x,y
